## 3. Database Schema & Data Models

PAC implements 7 core database models in a multi-relational layout supporting vector indexing, geospatial mapping, and graph syncing.

### Database Extensions
- **pgvector**: For 384-dimensional dense vector embeddings generated from crime MO narratives.
- **PostGIS**: For geospatial operations (`POINT` geometry using the standard SRID 4326 coordinate system).
- **uuid-ossp**: Generates non-sequential, secure primary keys.

### Entities & Relationships

| Table | Primary Key | Description | Relationships |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `users` | `UUID` | Police officers, supervisors, and admins. | `1-to-N` with `crimes` |
| `crimes` | `UUID` | Core FIR record with PostGIS `geom` and location details. | `1-to-1` with `crime_mo` & `crime_dna`; `N-to-M` with `criminals` & `victims` |
| `crime_mo` | `UUID` | Structured MO features extracted from narrative. | `1-to-1` with `crimes` |
| `criminals` | `UUID` | Suspect/accused profiles with identifiers and stats. | `N-to-M` with `crimes`; `1-to-1` with `behaviour_profiles` |
| `crime_criminals` | `UUID` | Association table linking crimes to accused/suspects. | Joint index linking `crimes` & `criminals` |
| `victims` | `UUID` | Victim profiles. | `N-to-M` with `crimes` |
| `crime_victims` | `UUID` | Association table tracking specific injury types and loss amounts. | Joint index linking `crimes` & `victims` |
| `crime_dna` | `UUID` | Semantic crime fingerprint vector (`vector(384)`). | `1-to-1` with `crimes` |
| `behaviour_profiles` | `UUID` | Aggregated behavioral habits of repeat offenders. | `1-to-1` with `criminals` |

